<paragraph blockId="20.[851,1376,675,697]" box="[851,1376,675,697]" pageId="20" pageNumber="717">
<heading box="[851,1376,675,697]" centered="true" fontSize="9" level="2" pageId="20" pageNumber="717" reason="2">
<taxonomicName authority="(WILLISTON, 1891)" baseAuthorityName="Williston" baseAuthorityYear="1891" box="[851,1376,675,697]" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Copestylum" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="20" pageNumber="717" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="quadratum">
<emphasis box="[851,1151,675,696]" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="717">COPESTYLUM QUADRATUM</emphasis>
(WILLISTON, 1891)
</taxonomicName>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="20.[806,1422,714,980]" pageId="20" pageNumber="717">
<emphasis box="[806,1072,714,735]" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="717">Larva and puparium:</emphasis>
Anterior fold with band of spicules narrowing towards the lateral ends. Longest vestiture of dorsum of prothorax longer than longest spicules on the anterior fold. Posterior breathing tube with AP about as long as wide above inconspicuous TR. AP tapering to about two-thirds of width of TR and 1.1¥ as long as TR is wide. Pupal spiracles about the same length as the AP and separated by about 1.3¥ their length with openings surrounding the apex.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="20" pageNumber="717" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="20.[806,1421,1024,1261]" pageId="20" pageNumber="717">
<emphasis box="[806,1310,1024,1046]" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="717">
Taxonomic notes: 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Williston" baseAuthorityYear="1891" box="[1030,1310,1024,1045]" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Copestylum" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="20" pageNumber="717" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="quadratum">Copestylum quadratum</taxonomicName>
</emphasis>
is most similar to 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Rotheray &amp; Marcos-García &amp; Hancock &amp; Pérez-Bañón &amp; Maier" authorityYear="2009" box="[924,1018,1055,1076]" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Copestylum" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="20" pageNumber="717" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="milae">
<emphasis box="[924,1018,1055,1076]" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="717">C. milae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
from which it differs by having the openings of the pupal spiracles surrounding the apex rather than being on the apex and by having the AP slightly longer than the TR is wide. 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Williston" baseAuthorityYear="1891" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Copestylum" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="20" pageNumber="717" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="quadratum">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="717">Copestylum quadratum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is separated from 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Rotheray &amp; Marcos-García &amp; Hancock &amp; Pérez-Bañón &amp; Maier" authorityYear="2009" box="[1172,1331,1177,1199]" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Copestylum" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="20" pageNumber="717" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="hidalgense">
<emphasis box="[1172,1331,1177,1199]" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="717">C. hidalgense</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by the absence of spicules on the anterodorsal margin of the mesothorax.
</paragraph>
